    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6498e5d9_c5bb30fc",
        "filename": "third_party/edo/BUILD.gn",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 11,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-30T18:47:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e This breaks EDO -- I tried.  Reverted it back to source_set.\n\nOK if it’s required.\n\n\u003e Why is it better as a static library?  Specifically it seemed like Service/Sources/NSKeyedArchiver+EDOAdditions.m was broken.\n\nsource_set means that the linker has to look at each object file. That’s not true in a static_library. That can increase link times and bloat output, but sometimes it’s necessary to force the linker to look at every object. (Actually, it happens somewhat often in Objective-C.)",
